avayaFabricAttachMib.name: avayaFabricAttachMib

revisions.description: Ver 28: Defined avFabricAttachDiscoveredElement and avFabricAttachExpiredElement notifications.

Ver 27: Updated avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientDetectTable index to support multiple detection data items per client type. A logic operation can also be specified to control data combinations (avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientDetectLogicOper).

Ver 26: Added avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientAttachExcludeStatic attribute to ZTC Attach table. Added new FA global statistics to export current binding counts in database. Introduced FA Client detection support through the avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientDetectTable.

Ver 25: Defined avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientAttachTable and the associated autoClientAttach Zero Touch option flag. NSV support is deprecated with this update. Updated avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientTable with avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientName and client origin (avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientOrigin) objects. Updated avFabricAttachIsidVlanAsgnsOrigin to support binding data originated through Zero Touch Client processing.
Ver 24: Added avFabricAttachZeroTouchNsvIsid attribute to the avFabricAttachZeroTouchNsvTable definition.
Ver 23: Added avFabricAttachStatsClearPortErrorCounters attribute. Updated description text for Fabric Attach statistics counters.
Ver 22: Added avFabricAttachPortMsgAuthKeymode attribute.
Ver 21: Added avFabricAttachDiscElemsAsgnsAuth. Added enum value none(4) for avFabricAttachDiscElemsElementAuth Changes requested by Zuyan Wang (VSP) - Prem
Ver 20: Reverted back the enum value invalid(1) to the original name other(1) for avFabricAttachDiscElemsElementType. Changes requested by Zuyan Wang (VSP) - Prem

Ver 19: Added avFabricAttachStats, avFabricAttachStatsClearErrorCounters, avFabricAttachStatsClearGlobalErrorCounters, avFabricAttachDiscElemsElementOperAuthStatus, avFabricAttachDiscElemsElementAsgnsOperAuthStatus, avFabricAttachStatsAsgnAuthFailed and avFabricAttachGlobalStatsAsgnAuthFailed. Renamed enum value other(1) to invalid(1) for avFabricAttachDiscElemsElementType. Renamed avFabricAttachStatsAuthFailed to avFabricAttachStatsDiscAuthFailed. Renamed avFabricAttachGlobalStatsAuthFailed to avFabricAttachGlobalStatsDiscAuthFailed Changes requested by Zuyan Wang (VSP) - Prem
Ver 18: Added avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientTable to support Zero Touch FA Client configuration.
Ver 17: Added avFabricAttachDiscElemsElementTrunkId attribute to export discovered element trunk associations.
Ver 16: Added autoPvidModeFaClient enumeration support for the avFabricAttachZeroTouchOptionFlags attribute.

Ver 15: Added avFabricAttachStatsDiscElemExpired, avFabricAttachStatsDiscElemDeleted and avFabricAttachStatsAsgnDeleted under AvFabricAttachStatsEntry. Also added avFabricAttachGlobalStatsDiscElemExpired, avFabricAttachGlobalStatsDiscElemDeleted and avFabricAttachGlobalStatsAsgnDeleted Changes requested by Zuyan Wang (VSP) - Prem

Ver 14: Added values faClientOnaSdn(16) and faClientOnaSpbOIp(17) to avFabricAttachElementType and avFabricAttachDiscElemsElementType. Added values provisionModeDisabled(2), provisionModeSpbm(3) and provisionModeVlan(4) to avFabricAttachDiscElemsElementState. Changed avFabricAttachTimeout to avFabricAttachAsgnTimeout. Added mib objects avFabricAttachDiscTimeout, avFabricAttachPortMgmtIsid and avFabricAttachPortMgmtCvid. Changes requested by Zuyan Wang (VSP) - Prem
Ver 13: Added avFabricAttachExtendedLogging attribute to control extended logging capabilities. Added binding source attribute to the avFabricAttachIsidVlanAsgnsTable.

Ver 12: Updated the avFabricAttachPortTable with per-port authentication attributes (avFabricAttachPortMsgAuthStatus, avFabricAttachPortMsgAuthKey). Updated discovered element authentication status enumerations. Updated statistics table object names by removing 'Sdk' to avoid confusion.
Ver 11: Added avFabricAttachTimeout, avFabricAttachSdkStatsTable, avFabricAttachGlobalSdkStats mib objects. Requested by Zuyan Wang for Fabric Attach on VSP8K (prempa).
Ver 10: Added standalone proxy attributes.
Ver 9: Added Zero Touch attribute definitions. Updated FA Discovered Elements table.
Ver 8: Updated attribute enumerations and naming. Updated FA Discovered Elements table.
Ver 7: Added Auto Provision support.
Ver 6: Updated FA element names in enumerations and object descriptions.
Ver 5: Added FA Discovered Elements table.
Ver 4: Added the ability to control host proxy operation. Expanded and clarified FA element types.
Ver 3: Added support for message authentication.
Ver 2: Added avFabricAttachPortTable and avFabricAttachAutoAttachService. Added RowStatus to IMPORTS.
Ver 1: Initial version.

avayaFabricAttachMib.description: This MIB module contains objects related to the Fabric Attach support.

avFabricAttachService.name: avFabricAttachService
avFabricAttachService.description: Exports the status of the Fabric Attach service.

avFabricAttachElementType.name: avFabricAttachElementType
avFabricAttachElementType.description: Exports the Fabric Attach element type indicating the services supported by the system. May be read-only on platforms that only support a single element type.

avFabricAttachPrimaryServerId.name: avFabricAttachPrimaryServerId
avFabricAttachPrimaryServerId.description: Exports primary server ID data on a FA Proxy if a primary server has been selected. A zero length string indicates that a primary server does not currently exist.

avFabricAttachPrimaryServerDescr.name: avFabricAttachPrimaryServerDescr
avFabricAttachPrimaryServerDescr.description: Exports a primary server description on a FA Proxy if a primary server has been selected.

avFabricAttachIsidVlanAsgnsTable.name: avFabricAttachIsidVlanAsgnsTable
avFabricAttachIsidVlanAsgnsTable.description: This table contains the I-SID <--> VLAN assignments for the Fabric Attach application.

avFabricAttachIsidVlanAsgnsEntry.name: avFabricAttachIsidVlanAsgnsEntry
avFabricAttachIsidVlanAsgnsEntry.description: Information about the I-SID <--> VLAN assignments for the Fabric Attach application.

avFabricAttachIsidVlanAsgnsIfIndex.name: avFabricAttachIsidVlanAsgnsIfIndex
avFabricAttachIsidVlanAsgnsIfIndex.description: Interface identifier component of the I-SID <-> VLAN assignment.

avFabricAttachIsidVlanAsgnsIsid.name: avFabricAttachIsidVlanAsgnsIsid
avFabricAttachIsidVlanAsgnsIsid.description: I-SID component of the I-SID <-> VLAN assignment.

avFabricAttachIsidVlanAsgnsVlan.name: avFabricAttachIsidVlanAsgnsVlan
avFabricAttachIsidVlanAsgnsVlan.description: VLAN ID component of the I-SID <-> VLAN assignment.

avFabricAttachIsidVlanAsgnsState.name: avFabricAttachIsidVlanAsgnsState
avFabricAttachIsidVlanAsgnsState.description: The current state of the Fabric Attach I-SID <-> VLAN assignment.

avFabricAttachIsidVlanAsgnsRowStatus.name: avFabricAttachIsidVlanAsgnsRowStatus
avFabricAttachIsidVlanAsgnsRowStatus.description: This object allows entries to be created and deleted in the avFabricAttachIsidVlanAsgnsTable.

avFabricAttachIsidVlanAsgnsOrigin.name: avFabricAttachIsidVlanAsgnsOrigin
avFabricAttachIsidVlanAsgnsOrigin.description: Origin information for the Fabric Attach I-SID <-> VLAN assignment.

avFabricAttachPortTable.name: avFabricAttachPortTable
avFabricAttachPortTable.description: This table contains port-specific data for the Fabric Attach application.

avFabricAttachPortEntry.name: avFabricAttachPortEntry
avFabricAttachPortEntry.description: Port-specific data related to the Fabric Attach application.

avFabricAttachPortState.name: avFabricAttachPortState
avFabricAttachPortState.description: The current port state from a Fabric Attach perspective. Indicates whether FA TLVs will be included in LLDPDUs generated on the port (enabled) or not (disabled).

avFabricAttachPortRowStatus.name: avFabricAttachPortRowStatus
avFabricAttachPortRowStatus.description: This object allows entries to be created, deleted and modified in the avFabricAttachPortTable, if the operation is supported by the agent.

avFabricAttachPortMsgAuthStatus.name: avFabricAttachPortMsgAuthStatus
avFabricAttachPortMsgAuthStatus.description: Controls the current Fabric Attach message authentication status for the associated interface.

avFabricAttachPortMsgAuthKey.name: avFabricAttachPortMsgAuthKey
avFabricAttachPortMsgAuthKey.description: Provides access to the Fabric Attach message authentication key for the associated interface. Can be used to establish a new key of length 1..32 octets. Always returns a zero-length string when queried.

avFabricAttachPortMgmtIsid.name: avFabricAttachPortMgmtIsid
avFabricAttachPortMgmtIsid.description: Fabric Attach management i-sid for the associated interface. Zero means the management i-sid feature is not enabled

avFabricAttachPortMgmtCvid.name: avFabricAttachPortMgmtCvid
avFabricAttachPortMgmtCvid.description: Fabric Attach management customer vid for the associated interface. Zero means the management i-sid feature is not enabled. 4096 means it is untagged

avFabricAttachPortMsgAuthKeymode.name: avFabricAttachPortMsgAuthKeymode
avFabricAttachPortMsgAuthKeymode.description: Controls the current Fabric Attach message authentication key-mode for the associated interface. A value of 'strict(1)' indicates that authentication using only the user-defined authentication key should be performed. A value of 'standard(2)' indicates that authentication using the user-defined authentication key as well as the default authentication key should be performed.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchService.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchService
avFabricAttachZeroTouchService.description: Controls the status of the Fabric Attach Zero Touch service.

avFabricAttachMsgAuthStatus.name: avFabricAttachMsgAuthStatus
avFabricAttachMsgAuthStatus.description: Controls the current Fabric Attach message authentication status.

avFabricAttachMsgAuthKey.name: avFabricAttachMsgAuthKey
avFabricAttachMsgAuthKey.description: Provides access to the Fabric Attach message authentication key. Can be used to establish a new key of length 1..32 octets. Always returns a zero-length string when queried.

avFabricAttachClientProxyStatus.name: avFabricAttachClientProxyStatus
avFabricAttachClientProxyStatus.description: Controls the current Fabric Attach client proxy status. A FA Proxy provides proxy services to FA Clients only when client proxy support is enabled.

avFabricAttachDiscElemsTable.name: avFabricAttachDiscElemsTable
avFabricAttachDiscElemsTable.description: This table contains details about locally connected Fabric Attach elements that have been discovered.

avFabricAttachDiscElemsEntry.name: avFabricAttachDiscElemsEntry
avFabricAttachDiscElemsEntry.description: Contains details about a locally connected Fabric Attach element.

avFabricAttachDiscElemsIfIndex.name: avFabricAttachDiscElemsIfIndex
avFabricAttachDiscElemsIfIndex.description: Identifies the interface through which the Fabric Attach element represented by this entry was discovered.

avFabricAttachDiscElemsElementType.name: avFabricAttachDiscElemsElementType
avFabricAttachDiscElemsElementType.description: Identifies the Fabric Attach element type as advertised through LLDP.

avFabricAttachDiscElemsElementVlan.name: avFabricAttachDiscElemsElementVlan
avFabricAttachDiscElemsElementVlan.description: Identifies the Fabric Attach element VLAN as advertised through LLDP.

avFabricAttachDiscElemsElementId.name: avFabricAttachDiscElemsElementId
avFabricAttachDiscElemsElementId.description: Exports the Chassis ID associated with the discovered Fabric Attach element as advertised through LLDP.

avFabricAttachDiscElemsElementState.name: avFabricAttachDiscElemsElementState
avFabricAttachDiscElemsElementState.description: Exports the state flag data associated with the discovered Fabric Attach element as advertised through LLDP.

avFabricAttachDiscElemsElementTrunkId.name: avFabricAttachDiscElemsElementTrunkId
avFabricAttachDiscElemsElementTrunkId.description: Identifies the trunk ID through which the Fabric Attach element represented by this entry was discovered.

avFabricAttachDiscElemsElementOperAuthSt.name: avFabricAttachDiscElemsElementOperAuthStatus
avFabricAttachDiscElemsElementOperAuthSt.description: the current operational Fabric Attach elements authentication status for the associated interface.

avFabricAttachDiscElemsElementAsgnsOperA.name: avFabricAttachDiscElemsElementAsgnsOperAuthStatus
avFabricAttachDiscElemsElementAsgnsOperA.description: the current operational Fabric Attach assignment authentication status for the associated interface.

avFabricAttachAutoProvision.name: avFabricAttachAutoProvision
avFabricAttachAutoProvision.description: Exports the Fabric Attach Auto Provision setting indicating the services supported by the system. May be read-only on platforms that don't support this functionality.

avFabricAttachProvisionMode.name: avFabricAttachProvisionMode
avFabricAttachProvisionMode.description: Exports the Fabric Attach provision mode.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchOptionFlags.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchOptionFlags
avFabricAttachZeroTouchOptionFlags.description: Exports the Zero Touch option data.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchNsvTable.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchNsvTable
avFabricAttachZeroTouchNsvTable.description: This table contains the Zero Touch NSV specifications for the Fabric Attach application.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchNsvEntry.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchNsvEntry
avFabricAttachZeroTouchNsvEntry.description: Information about the Zero Touch NSV specifications for the Fabric Attach application.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchNsvType.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchNsvType
avFabricAttachZeroTouchNsvType.description: Element type identifier component of the NSV specification.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchNsvVlan.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchNsvVlan
avFabricAttachZeroTouchNsvVlan.description: VLAN ID component of the NSV specification.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchNsvPortPriority.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchNsvPortPriority
avFabricAttachZeroTouchNsvPortPriority.description: Port priority component of the NSV specification.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchNsvStateFlags.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchNsvStateFlags
avFabricAttachZeroTouchNsvStateFlags.description: State flags associated with the NSV specification.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchNsvRowStatus.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchNsvRowStatus
avFabricAttachZeroTouchNsvRowStatus.description: This object allows entries to be created and deleted in the avFabricAttachZeroTouchNsvTable.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchNsvIsid.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchNsvIsid
avFabricAttachZeroTouchNsvIsid.description: I-SID component of the NSV specification. A value of 0 indicates that an I-SID has not been specified.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchRadiusPriSrvrIpv4.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchRadiusPriSrvrIpv4Addr
avFabricAttachZeroTouchRadiusPriSrvrIpv4.description: This object represents the Zero Touch RADIUS primary server IPv4 address information currently maintained by the FA agent.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchRadiusSecSrvrIpv4.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchRadiusSecSrvrIpv4Addr
avFabricAttachZeroTouchRadiusSecSrvrIpv4.description: This object represents the Zero Touch RADIUS secondary server IPv4 address information currently maintained by the FA agent.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchRadiusTimeout.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchRadiusTimeout
avFabricAttachZeroTouchRadiusTimeout.description: This object represents the Zero Touch RADIUS timeout information currently maintained by the FA agent.

avFabricAttachStandaloneProxy.name: avFabricAttachStandaloneProxy
avFabricAttachStandaloneProxy.description: Controls the standalone FA Proxy mode.

avFabricAttachAsgnTimeout.name: avFabricAttachAsgnTimeout
avFabricAttachAsgnTimeout.description: Exports the Fabric Attach assignment timeout.

avFabricAttachStatsTable.name: avFabricAttachStatsTable
avFabricAttachStatsTable.description: This table contains Fabric Attach port statistics data.

avFabricAttachStatsEntry.name: avFabricAttachStatsEntry
avFabricAttachStatsEntry.description: Each entry contains Fabric Attach operational statistics for a specific device port. Ports are identified by their MIB II ifIndex value.

avFabricAttachStatsPortIndex.name: avFabricAttachStatsPortIndex
avFabricAttachStatsPortIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a port. This value corresponds to a MIB II ifIndex.

avFabricAttachStatsDiscElemReceived.name: avFabricAttachStatsDiscElemReceived
avFabricAttachStatsDiscElemReceived.description: Indicates the number of FA Element TLVs received on the identified port.

avFabricAttachStatsAsgnReceived.name: avFabricAttachStatsAsgnReceived
avFabricAttachStatsAsgnReceived.description: Indicates the number of I-SID/VLAN bindings received in FA I-SID/VLAN Assignment TLVs on the identified port.

avFabricAttachStatsAsgnAccepted.name: avFabricAttachStatsAsgnAccepted
avFabricAttachStatsAsgnAccepted.description: Indicates the number of I-SID/VLAN bindings from received FA I-SID/VLAN Assignment TLVs that are accepted (activated) on the identified port. Counter is incremented when the binding transitions from a non-accepted state (e.g., 'pending', 'rejected') to the accepted state.

avFabricAttachStatsAsgnRejected.name: avFabricAttachStatsAsgnRejected
avFabricAttachStatsAsgnRejected.description: Indicates the number of I-SID/VLAN bindings from received FA I-SID/VLAN Assignment TLVs that are rejected on the identified port. Counter is incremented when the binding transitions from a non-rejected state (e.g., 'pending', 'accepted') to the rejected state.

avFabricAttachStatsAsgnExpired.name: avFabricAttachStatsAsgnExpired
avFabricAttachStatsAsgnExpired.description: Indicates the number of I-SID/VLAN bindings from received FA I-SID/VLAN Assignment TLVs that have expired on the identified port. Counter is not incremented when bindings are deleted for reasons other than expiration.

avFabricAttachStatsDiscAuthFailed.name: avFabricAttachStatsDiscAuthFailed
avFabricAttachStatsDiscAuthFailed.description: Indicates the number of received FA Element TLVs for which authentication was attempted and failed on the identified port.

avFabricAttachStatsDiscElemExpired.name: avFabricAttachStatsDiscElemExpired
avFabricAttachStatsDiscElemExpired.description: Indicates the number of discovered FA elements from received FA Element TLVs that have expired on the identified port. Counter is not incremented when elements are deleted for reasons other than expiration.

avFabricAttachStatsDiscElemDeleted.name: avFabricAttachStatsDiscElemDeleted
avFabricAttachStatsDiscElemDeleted.description: Indicates the number of discovered FA elements from received FA Element TLVs that have been deleted on the identified port. Counter is only incremented when elements are deleted for reasons other than expiration.

avFabricAttachStatsAsgnDeleted.name: avFabricAttachStatsAsgnDeleted
avFabricAttachStatsAsgnDeleted.description: Indicates the number of I-SID/VLAN bindings from received FA I-SID/VLAN Assignment TLVs that have been deleted on the identified port. Counter is only incremented when bindings are deleted for reasons other than expiration.

avFabricAttachStatsAsgnAuthFailed.name: avFabricAttachStatsAsgnAuthFailed
avFabricAttachStatsAsgnAuthFailed.description: Indicates the number of received FA I-SID/VLAN Assignment TLVs for which authentication was attempted and failed on the identified port.

avFabricAttachGlobalStatsDiscElemReceive.name: avFabricAttachGlobalStatsDiscElemReceived
avFabricAttachGlobalStatsDiscElemReceive.description: Indicates the number of FA Element TLVs received on all device ports since the most recent epoch (e.g., device reset, global statistics reset).

avFabricAttachGlobalStatsAsgnReceived.name: avFabricAttachGlobalStatsAsgnReceived
avFabricAttachGlobalStatsAsgnReceived.description: Indicates the number of I-SID/VLAN bindings received in FA I-SID/VLAN Assignment TLVs on all device ports since the most recent epoch (e.g., device reset, global statistics reset).

avFabricAttachGlobalStatsAsgnAccepted.name: avFabricAttachGlobalStatsAsgnAccepted
avFabricAttachGlobalStatsAsgnAccepted.description: Indicates the number of I-SID/VLAN bindings from received FA I-SID/VLAN Assignment TLVs that are accepted (activated) on all device ports since the most recent epoch (e.g., device reset, global statistics reset). Counter is incremented when the binding transitions from a non-accepted state (e.g., 'pending', 'rejected') to the accepted state.

avFabricAttachGlobalStatsAsgnRejected.name: avFabricAttachGlobalStatsAsgnRejected
avFabricAttachGlobalStatsAsgnRejected.description: Indicates the number of I-SID/VLAN bindings from received FA I-SID/VLAN Assignment TLVs that are rejected on all device ports since the most recent epoch (e.g., device reset, global statistics reset). Counter is incremented when the binding transitions from a non-rejected state (e.g., 'pending', 'accepted') to the rejected state.

avFabricAttachGlobalStatsAsgnExpired.name: avFabricAttachGlobalStatsAsgnExpired
avFabricAttachGlobalStatsAsgnExpired.description: Indicates the number of I-SID/VLAN bindings from received FA I-SID/VLAN Assignment TLVs that have expired on all device ports since the most recent epoch (e.g., device reset, global statistics reset). Counter is not incremented when bindings are deleted for reasons other than expiration.

avFabricAttachGlobalStatsDiscAuthFailed.name: avFabricAttachGlobalStatsDiscAuthFailed
avFabricAttachGlobalStatsDiscAuthFailed.description: Indicates the number of received FA Element TLVs for which authentication was attempted and failed on all device ports since the most recent epoch (e.g., device reset, global statistics reset).

avFabricAttachGlobalStatsDiscElemExpired.name: avFabricAttachGlobalStatsDiscElemExpired
avFabricAttachGlobalStatsDiscElemExpired.description: Indicates the number of discovered FA elements from received FA Element TLVs that have been deleted on all device ports since the most recent epoch (e.g., device reset, global statistics reset). Counter is only incremented when elements are deleted for reasons other than expiration.

avFabricAttachGlobalStatsDiscElemDeleted.name: avFabricAttachGlobalStatsDiscElemDeleted
avFabricAttachGlobalStatsDiscElemDeleted.description: Indicates the number of discovered FA elements from received FA Element TLVs that have been deleted on all device ports since the most recent epoch (e.g., device reset, global statistics reset). Counter is only incremented when elements are deleted for reasons other than expiration.

avFabricAttachGlobalStatsAsgnDeleted.name: avFabricAttachGlobalStatsAsgnDeleted
avFabricAttachGlobalStatsAsgnDeleted.description: Indicates the number of I-SID/VLAN bindings from received FA I-SID/VLAN Assignment TLVs that have been deleted on all device ports since the most recent epoch (e.g., device reset, global statistics reset). Counter is only incremented when bindings are deleted for reasons other than expiration.

avFabricAttachGlobalStatsAsgnAuthFailed.name: avFabricAttachGlobalStatsAsgnAuthFailed
avFabricAttachGlobalStatsAsgnAuthFailed.description: Indicates the number of received FA I-SID/VLAN Assignment TLVs for which authentication was attempted and failed on all device ports since the most recent epoch (e.g., device reset, global statistics reset).

avFabricAttachGlobalStatsCurReceivedBind.name: avFabricAttachGlobalStatsCurReceivedBindings
avFabricAttachGlobalStatsCurReceivedBind.description: Indicates the number of received FA I-SID/VLAN bindings currently maintained in the database.

avFabricAttachGlobalStatsCurAdvertisedBi.name: avFabricAttachGlobalStatsCurAdvertisedBindings
avFabricAttachGlobalStatsCurAdvertisedBi.description: Indicates the number of FA I-SID/VLAN bindings that are currently being advertised (service requests).

avFabricAttachExtendedLogging.name: avFabricAttachExtendedLogging
avFabricAttachExtendedLogging.description: Controls the Fabric Attach extended logging capabilities.

avFabricAttachDiscTimeout.name: avFabricAttachDiscTimeout
avFabricAttachDiscTimeout.description: Exports the Fabric Attach discovery timeout.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientTable.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientTable
avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientTable.description: This table contains the Zero Touch Client specifications for the Fabric Attach application.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientEntry.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientEntry
avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientEntry.description: Information about the Zero Touch Client specifications for the Fabric Attach application.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientType.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientType
avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientType.description: FA Element type identifier component of the Client specification.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientDescr.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientDescr
avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientDescr.description: Client description for the Client specification.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientOptionFlags.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientOptionFlags
avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientOptionFlags.description: Zero Touch options associated with the Client specification. Supported values are synchronized with the Zero Touch options available through the avFabricAttachZeroTouchOptionFlags attribute.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientRowStatus.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientRowStatus
avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientRowStatus.description: This object allows entries to be created, deleted and modified in the avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientTable.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientName.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientName
avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientName.description: Client name for the Client specification.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientOrigin.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientOrigin
avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientOrigin.description: Client origin information. Clients may be well-known ('standard(1)') devices that utilize FA signaling. If supported, clients may also be user-defined ('custom(2)') devices that are typically identified by means other than FA signaling. Standard clients are pre-populated in the table and support limited modifications.

avFabricAttachStatsClearErrorCounters.name: avFabricAttachStatsClearErrorCounters
avFabricAttachStatsClearErrorCounters.description: Clears Fabric Attach statistic and error counters on all device interfaces. Setting this attribute to 'true(1)' clears all counters. The value 'false(2)' is returned when the attribute is queried.

avFabricAttachStatsClearGlobalErrorCount.name: avFabricAttachStatsClearGlobalErrorCounters
avFabricAttachStatsClearGlobalErrorCount.description: Clears Fabric Attach statistic and error global (summary) counters. Setting this attribute to 'true(1)' clears all summary counters. The value 'false(2)' is returned when the attribute is queried.

avFabricAttachStatsClearPortErrorCounter.name: avFabricAttachStatsClearPortErrorCounters
avFabricAttachStatsClearPortErrorCounter.description: Clears Fabric Attach statistic and error counters for a specific interface. Setting this attribute to an ifIndex value identifying a device interface clears the counters associated with the interface. The value 0 is returned when the attribute is queried.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientAttachTable.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientAttachTable
avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientAttachTable.description: This table contains the Zero Touch Client auto-attach specifications for the Fabric Attach application.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientAttachEntry.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientAttachEntry
avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientAttachEntry.description: Information about the Zero Touch Client auto-attach specifications for the Fabric Attach application.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientAttachType.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientAttachType
avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientAttachType.description: Element type identifier component of the Zero Touch Client auto-attach specification.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientAttachVlan.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientAttachVlan
avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientAttachVlan.description: VLAN ID component of the Zero Touch Client auto-attach specification. A value of 4096 indicates that a VLAN has not been specified (e.g., an untagged traffic environment).

avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientAttachPortP.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientAttachPortPriority
avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientAttachPortP.description: Port priority component of the Zero Touch Client auto-attach specification. A value of 8 indicates that a port priority has not been specified.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientAttachIsid.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientAttachIsid
avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientAttachIsid.description: I-SID component of the Zero Touch Client auto-attach specification. A value of 0 indicates that an I-SID has not been specified.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientAttachRowSt.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientAttachRowStatus
avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientAttachRowSt.description: This object allows entries to be created and deleted in the avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientAttachTable.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientAttachExclu.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientAttachExcludeStatic
avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientAttachExclu.description: Indicates if static VLANs associated with the client interface should be removed while the client is connected to the device.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientDetectTable.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientDetectTable
avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientDetectTable.description: This table contains the Zero Touch Client detection specifications for the Fabric Attach application.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientDetectEntry.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientDetectEntry
avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientDetectEntry.description: Information about the Zero Touch Client detection specifications for the Fabric Attach application.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientDetectType.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientDetectType
avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientDetectType.description: Element type identifier component of the Zero Touch Client detection specification.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientDetectMetho.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientDetectMethod
avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientDetectMetho.description: Specifies the detection method used to identify custom Zero Touch Clients.

avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientDetectData.name: avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientDetectData
avFabricAttachZeroTouchClientDetectData.description: Specifies the data that is used to identify custom Zero Touch Clients. Data application depends on the associated detection method.
